SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04471538
Version: 1

HPSBHF03125 rev.1 - HP Next Generation Firewall (NGFW) running Bash Shell,
Remote Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2014-10-15
Last Updated: 2014-10-15

Potential Security Impact: Remote code execution

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP Next
Generation Firewall (NGFW) running Bash Shell. This is the Bash Shell
vulnerability known as "ShellShock" which could be exploited remotely to
allow execution of code.

NOTE: This vulnerability can only be exploited if the attacker already has
valid administrative login credentials.

References:

  CVE-2014-6271
  CVE-2014-6277
  CVE-2014-6278
  CVE-2014-7169
  CVE-2014-7186
  CVE-2014-7187
  SSRT101724

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Next Generation Firewall (NGFW) - All released versions including:

  v1.1.0.4150
  v1.1.0.4127
  v1.0.3.4024
  v1.0.2.3988
  v1.0.1.3974

